TY  - JOUR
AU  - De Haas, Ralph
AU  - Van Horen, Neeltje
T1  - Running for the Exit? International Bank Lending During a Financial Crisis
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhs113
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 26
IS  - 1
SP  - 244
EP  - 285
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We use loan-level data to examine how large international banks reduced their cross-border lending after the collapse of Lehman Brothers. Country, firm, and bank fixed effects allow us to disentangle credit supply and demand and to simultaneously control for the unobserved traits of banks and the countries and firms they lend to. We document substantial heterogeneity in the extent to which different banks retrenched from the same country. Banks reduced credit less to markets that were geographically close; where they were more experienced; where they operated a subsidiary; and where they were integrated into a network of domestic co-lenders.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhs113
ER  - 



